The augmented matrix below for a linear system is put in reduced row
echelon form with row operations. Write one of the following:

\begin{itemize}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  the solution if it is unique
\item
  all solutions if there are more than one
\item
  state that there are no solutions.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{(a)}

\begin{align*}\left[\begin{array}{ccc}0 & 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & 0 \end{array}\right. \left| \begin{array}{c} 0 \\ 0 \\ 0 \end{array}\right]\end{align*}
